article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast 76, Lipscomb 73
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. -- Derrick O'Neil had 17 points, including a go-ahead layup with 26 seconds remaining to lift Florida Gulf Coast past Lipscomb 76-73 on Monday night. Down 73-71 with 32 seconds left, FGC's Reggie Chambers split his free throws and Chambers grabbed his 12th rebound (sixth offensive board) of the game on the miss. O'Neil got the ball back in the same posession to put the Eagles (10-15, 6-8 Atlantic Sun Conference) back in the lead. Michael Lusk missed a shot with 13 seconds left, and turned the ball over with 2 seconds to go after a Lipscomb (8-13, 4-8) offensive rebound. Reed Baker hit two free throws with 1 second left, sealing the game for FGC. Baker led the Eagles with 23 points and Kyle Marks added 15. Four players scored in double figures for Lipscomb as Adnan Hodzic had 15, Josh Slater 14, Lusk 13 and Jordan Burgason 10.
